The article is a transcript of an on-background conference call about the President's discretionary funding request for fiscal year 2022. The call was conducted by administration officials and was embargoed until 11:00 a.m. Eastern time. The officials discussed the President's goals for the funding request, which include reversing the underinvestment in public services and programs over the past decade. They highlighted key investments in areas such as education, public health, climate change, housing, and gun violence prevention. The funding request includes $769 billion for non-defense discretionary spending, a 16% increase over fiscal year 2021. The officials emphasized that this request is separate from the President's infrastructure package and that the full budget, including detailed proposals, will be released in the coming months. They also addressed questions about negotiation, paying for the funding levels, and outreach to Congress.